<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVID TOUFIC MIZRAHI; EDITOR WAS EXPERT ON MIDEAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Toufic Mizrahi, 64, editor and publisher of the New York-based newsletter 
MidEast Report who was frequently quoted in various publications after Iraq's 
invasion of Kuwait on Aug. 2. Regarded as an authority on oil and Middle East 
politics, Mizrahi regularly appeared on network television news shows, 
including PBS' "The MacNeil/Lehrer Newshour." 
</P>
<P>
During the current crisis, he had been quoted by major newspapers and news 
magazines on the economic and political conditions in Iraq and Kuwait. Mizrahi 
was born in Beirut and earned a law degree at the Sorbonne in Paris. He moved 
to the United States in 1960 and worked as a foreign correspondent in New York 
and Washington for several Middle East newspapers. In 1967, Mizrahi founded his 
MidEast Report newsletter, which is published every two weeks. On Friday of 
complications of pneumonia and cancer in New York City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
