<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old man was in critical condition after being shot in the chest while 
allegedly trying to break into a Mission Beach apartment early Sunday, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The occupant of the apartment in the 800 block of San Jose Place was awakened 
about 3:31 a.m. by noise and armed himself with a shotgun when he heard someone 
attempting to break in the front door, police said. 
</P>
<P>
When the door burst open, the occupant fired one shot at the suspect, Andrew 
Weisiger, hitting him in the chest. Weisiger was taken to Scripps Memorial 
Hospital in La Jolla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
