<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 28-year-old woman was in custody Sunday after allegedly stabbing a pregnant 
woman outside a Logan Heights bar, police said. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, both the victim and the suspect were inside the Aztec Bar 
at 2950 National Ave. Patricia Camargo-Beltran, 27, who is three months 
pregnant, left the bar at 1:59 a.m. Sunday and Martha Barron followed her. An 
argument ensued, and Barron stabbed Camargo-Beltran in the stomach, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Camargo-Beltran was in good condition late Sunday at UC San Diego Medical 
Center. 
