<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERGEANT, PARTY-GOER WOUNDED IN MELEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles police sergeant and a gun-wielding party-goer were wounded in a 
melee at a party Saturday night on East 25th Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Steve Richards, 34, shot in the left thigh, was in satisfactory condition 
Sunday at Santa Marta Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel Najera, 26, was booked on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon at 
the jail ward of County-USC Medical Center, where he was in stable condition, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Newton Division officers were called to investigate shots fired at the party, 
which police said was attended by up to 50 people. 
</P>
<P>
The officers were in an alley behind the residence when a shot rang out, 
wounding Richards, Lt. Charles Massey said. Officers returned fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
