<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New and Winning Voices: Two tenors, Brian Asawa and George Ingram III, shared 
top honors in the Western Regional Finals of the Metropolitan Opera auditions 
held Friday night at USC and will compete for contracts with the opera company 
at the national finals next spring. 
</P>
<P>
Asawa, 24, a countertenor from Los Angeles, took home a cash prize of $3,400, 
as did tenor Ingram, 23, of Tucson. Second prize of $2,300 went to baritone 
Earl Patriarco, 23, of Whittier. Chief judge in the regional finals was soprano 
Carol Neblett, representing the Met. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
