<HEADLINE>
<P>
LUTHER CAMPBELL'S LYRICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luther Campbell self-righteously puts an "adult" sticker on the album and hides 
behind his claim of comedy ("Today They're Trying to Censor Rap, Tomorrow. . . 
," Nov. 5). 
</P>
<P>
Since when is it entertainment to tear open women's vaginas, bust the walls, 
break their backbones? 
</P>
<P>
They call this comedy? I call it rape, and rape and sexual violence aren't 
funny. Ask the runner in Central Park. 
</P>
<P>
KATHY SILVERI 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111290-0035 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 306724 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 12, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
