</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dave Lesher and Janet Eastman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOT PROPERTY: "Love You to Death," a television miniseries recounting the 
bizarre David Brown murder case, is in production in L.A. and due to air by 
spring. 
</P>
<P>
Republic Pictures is billing the plot as "one of the most shocking crimes of 
the decade." . . . Brown, an Anaheim Hills computer entrepreneur, is serving a 
life sentence for persuading his 14-year-old daughter to murder his fifth wife. 
The girl went to prison for four years while Brown collected his dead wife's 
life insurance and married her sister. Dave Lesher and Janet Eastman 
</P>
