<TEXT>
<P>
ON THE JOB: Ken Weir, the Santa Ana test pilot, is still flying, climbing to 
over 60,000 feet in a U-2 last week. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm the only guy over 60 who's ever been over 60," he cracked. . . . Lockheed 
tried to ground Weir when he turned 60, but he sued. Although a Chicago court 
last week upheld a similar age limit for airline pilots, Weir's lawyers say 
they'll have an easier time. Boeing has agreed to raise its test-pilot age 
limit, "and we're negotiating with every other airframe manufacturer," said a 
lawyer. Dave Lesher and Janet Eastman 
</P>
