<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
LECTURES TO FOCUS ON DOMESTIC VIOLENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Coast College will offer a series of free lectures on domestic violence 
Tuesday through Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Best-selling author Paxton Quigley highlights the series with a presentation 
Wednesday at 11 a.m. Quigley, author of "Armed and Female," will discuss 
personal protection strategies for women, including firearms for self-defense. 
She is a certified instructor with the National Rifle Assn. and teaches 
gun-defense classes for women. 
</P>
<P>
Other lectures will focus on the court system, alcohol and drug abuse, the 
effects of domestic violence on children and the need for shelters. 
</P>
<P>
All sessions will be held in the Student Center Lounge. 
</P>
<P>
For a schedule or more information on the lectures, call (714) 432-5727. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111290-0043 </DOCNO>
