<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEEN KILLED IN CRASH WITH SUSPECTED DRUNK DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age girl was fatally injured and her two companions were hurt when a 
driver suspected of being drunk crashed into the back of their car as they 
waited for a traffic light in Redondo Beach early Sunday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Brady Grasinger, 15, of Rancho Palos Verdes was a passenger in a 
car stopped at 177th Street and Hawthorne Boulevard that was rear-ended shortly 
before 3 a.m. The driver and another passenger, both teen-agers from Rancho 
Palos Verdes, were treated for minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Grasinger was taken to South Bay Hospital, where she died about 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Raul Sanchez Ramirez, 27, of Lawndale at the scene. He was 
booked at Redondo Beach jail on suspicion of felony drunk driving and held in 
lieu of $25,000 bail. 
</P>
