<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Hazardous Materials Team, administered by the county Health 
Care Agency's division of environmental health, responds to calls on chemical 
spills and other incidents involving hazardous materials. Sometimes the team 
goes to the site and other times it advises citizens or local fire departments 
over the phone. 
</P>
<P>
There were 29 spills recorded in HAZMAT's response logs in September. The 
following details the seven spills that occurred in the Costa Mesa/Newport 
Beach/Irvine area of the county. 
</P>
