Photo, Rolling In the Money: More than 8,000 motorcyclists, including comedian 
Jay Leno, rode more than 100 circuitous miles Sunday from Glendale to Malibu to 
raise $825,000 for the Muscular Dystrophy Assn. Leno's Harley-Davidson, above 
left, was featured in an auction conducted by Leno, above right, and brought in 
$7,500 from David Oakleaf of Long Beach. Jackson Browne, below left, plays a 
few chords for Muscular Dystrophy poster child Jason Baringer, 9, of Palos 
Verdes, before entertaining the crowd with a set. Motorcycles fill the parking 
lot at Calamigos Ranch in Malibu Canyon, below right, with gleaming chrome. The 
Love Ride 7, as it was billed, is said to be the largest motorcycle 
fund-raising event in the nation. Participants pledged a minimum of $40. The 
ride was sponsored by Harley-Davidson of Glendale and was the most successful 
one of its seven-year history. At times the line of motorcycles, escorted by 
the California Highway Patrol, stretched three miles. ROLANDO OTERO / Los 
Angeles Times 
