<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OLAJUWON'S WAKE-UP CALL SPURS ROCKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a heartbreaking loss the night before at San Antonio, the Houston Rockets 
didn't appear to be ready when their game against Utah began Sunday night at 
Houston. 
</P>
<P>
So, the Jazz jumped in front early by 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
But Akeem Olajuwon woke up the Rockets and by the second half they were flying. 
They romped to a 110-90 victory, pulling Houston to .500 (3-3). 
</P>
<P>
Olajuwon scored 15 points in the first quarter and finished with 31 points and 
21 rebounds. He scored seven in a 21-2 run that broke the game open in the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Minnesota 108, Orlando 81 -- The Timberwolves are beating up on other expansion 
teams. Friday they trounced Charlotte, 106-77. 
</P>
<P>
In this rout of Orlando (0-6) at Minneapolis, the Wolves broke it open with a 
30-10 spurt in the third quarter. Tony Campbell had eight of his 24 in the 
spurt. 
</P>
<P>
The Magic have lost 21 of their past 22 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
