<P>
Qantas Cuts Jobs: Australia's international airline will slash jobs in a bid to 
remain competitive, chief executive John Ward said. It will cut 500 from its 
work force of 17,000 by March 1 and sell five Boeing 747 aircraft earlier than 
planned, bringing to nine the number to be sold in the next 18 months. The 
Labor government said it planned to sell 49% of the state-owned carrier and 
would let foreign investors own up to 35% of Qantas. 
