LANSDALE, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joseph Cicippio Jr., son of an American held hostage in Lebanon, died Sunday of 
a heart attack at age 35, hospital officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
Cicippio was taken to North Penn Hospital early Sunday morning, a nursing 
supervisor said. He was pronounced dead at 6:29 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Family members refused to talk to reporters today and funeral arrangements were 
incomplete. 
</P>
<P>
Joseph Cicippio Sr. was taken hostage in Beirut on Sept. 12, 1986. His son 
became the third member of his family to die since he was taken into captivity. 
A sister, Rose Abell, 73, died of cancer months after his kidnaping. Abell's 
husband, Bill, 80, died last year of a heart attack. 
