<P>
TOPANGA FIRE CHARS 40 ACRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A brush fire that erupted before dawn today in a Topanga Canyon clearing that 
teen-agers use as a hangout scorched 40 acres and shut down a canyon road but 
damaged no structures, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire began about 3:50 a.m. near Old Topanga Canyon and Zuniga roads. By 7 
a.m., about 200 firefighters had the blaze encircled, Los Angeles County Fire 
Capt. Frank Lopez said. 
</P>
<P>
One minor injury was reported to a firefighter working on an inmate crew. The 
fire's cause was not immediately pinpointed, but an illegal campfire was 
suspected. 
</P>
