<P>
ABC WILL AIR USC-UCLA AT ROSE BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although lacking its usual Rose Bowl ramifications, ABC announced today that it 
will televise Saturday's USC-UCLA game. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Jackson and Bob Griese will call the 12:30 p.m. game from the Rose Bowl 
that will air live on Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42 in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
The game will be shown nationwide, except in most of the Midwest. 
</P>
<P>
Last week, ABC said it would televise either the USC-UCLA or 
Washington-Washington State games. However, the latter game lost much of its 
luster Saturday when the then-second-ranked Huskies were upset by UCLA, 25-22, 
and Notre Dame kept its spot atop the Associated Press poll with a 34-29 win 
over Tennessee. 
</P>
<P>
Had ABC opted against showing USC-UCLA, the game could have aired on cable's 
Prime Ticket Network, which owns the cable rights to Pacific 10 Conference 
games. 
