<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
ABC CANCELS STEVEN BOCHCO'S EXPERIMENTAL SERIES 'COP ROCK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stephen Bochco's "Cop Rock," the police show set to music, has been canceled 
after its Dec. 26 broadcast, ABC announced today. 
</P>
<P>
The series from the creator of "L.A. Law" and "Hill Street Blues," was an 
experimental series that tried to use four or five musical numbers per hourlong 
episode to push the plot along in a sort of musical "Hill Street." 
</P>
<P>
Robert A. Iger, president of ABC Entertainment, said in making the 
announcement: 
</P>
<P>
"In 'Cop Rock' Stephen Bochco delivered a daring and brilliantly produced 
series, one all of us at ABC are proud to be associated with." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
